-- Turkey's Sabanci to bid for some assets of Lafarge-Holcim portfolio-source
-- By Ebru Tuncay
-- Tue Sep 23, 2014 07:00AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Sept 23 (Reuters) - Turkish conglomerate Sabanci Holding <SAHOL.IS> plans to bid for some of the assets that cement makers Lafarge <LAFP.PA> and Holcim <HOLN.VX> must sell to steer their mega-merger past competition watchdogs, a source with knowledge of the deal told Reuters.

"Sabanci Cement Group is interested in these sales. Preparations are being made to make a bid in December. Before the bid, preliminary information has been obtained on the assets so it can be assessed," the source said.